  "summary": "metavu exfiltrates installer system identity via preinstall hook",
  "details": "package.json declares `preinstall: node index.js`, which fires automatically on `npm install`. index.js executes `whoami`, `id`, and `pwd`, gathers hostname, platform, arch, homedir, username, uid, gid, shell, and OS details, and POSTs the resulting JSON to the hardcoded URL `https://4f54203c-996c-4f52-b136-ef9b1fd0f64d/detox56` (index.js line 6 / line 51). The package has empty author/description/license metadata and ships an unrelated file `i` containing scraped Instagram data, with no advertised library functionality. Installing the package leaks installer identity and host fingerprint to an attacker-controlled endpoint with no user interaction.",
